{{pp-move-indef}} {{dablink|This article is about the bodies of water. For other uses, see [[Sea (disambiguation)]] and [[SEA (disambiguation)]]}} [[File:Waves lajolla.jpg|thumb|right|300px|The sea at [[La Jolla, California]] in the [[Gulf of Catalina]]]] A '''sea''' generally refers to a large [[body of water|body]] of salt water, but the term is used in other contexts as well. Most commonly, it means a large expanse of [[salinity|saline water]] connected with an [[ocean]], and is commonly used as a synonym for [[ocean]].<ref>http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/sea</ref> It is also used sometimes to describe a large saline [[lake]] that lacks a natural outlet, such as the [[Caspian Sea]].
